                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-353-off1817 t18280911-353-cd1818"></join>, 1 coat, value 5s.; 1 waistcoat, value 2s.; and 1 pair of trousers, value 2s.
            </rs>; the goods of 
               <persName id="t18280911-353-victim1912" type="victimName">
                  Richard 
                  Marshall
               <interp inst="t18280911-353-victim1912" type="surname" value="Marshall"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-353-victim1912" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-353-victim1912" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-353-off1817 t18280911-353-victim1912"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>RICHARD MARSHALL. I am a <rs id="t18280911-353-viclabel1819" type="occupation">blacksmith</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-353-victim1912 t18280911-353-viclabel1819"></join>, and live in Frederick-street. I lent my coat, waistcoat, and trousers, to Edward Potter, on the 21st of July; I was to have five shillings for the use of them for about an hour - I have never seen them since.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-353-person1913">
                  EDWARD 
                  POTTER
               <interp inst="t18280911-353-person1913" type="surname" value="POTTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-353-person1913" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-353-person1913" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I borrowed this coat, waistcoat, and trousers of Richard Marshall for the prisoner; I lent them to him - I told Marshall they were for a young man, but I did not say his name - the prisoner never returned them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-353-person1914">
                  WILLIAM 
                  POTTER
               <interp inst="t18280911-353-person1914" type="surname" value="POTTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-353-person1914" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-353-person1914" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I met the prisoner in Weymouth-street, on the Wednesday; he said, the articles were left at a friend of his, and if I went with him I should have them - I went with him to Benjamin's, a salesman's shop, and he said, he had sent a person to sell them there; that he stood in the street, and got the money, 3s. 6d.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-353-person1915">
                  SOLOMON 
                  MOSES
               <interp inst="t18280911-353-person1915" type="surname" value="MOSES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-353-person1915" type="given" value="SOLOMON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-353-person1915" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mrs. Benjamin; she is a widow - I bought a coat and waistcoat for five shillings of a young man - I did not see the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-353-person1916">
                  HENRY 
                  RICHARD BUCKERIDGE
               <interp inst="t18280911-353-person1916" type="surname" value="RICHARD BUCKERIDGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-353-person1916" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-353-person1916" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took up the prisoner; he had these trousers on, and said he had sold the coat and waistcoat to a young man, well-known at the Olive-branch public-house, but I could not find him; as he went to the office, he said, he wished he had taken my advice before.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280911-353-verdict1820" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-353-verdict1820" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
